stanford law review goes online stanford law school stanford law school search utility navigation test directory news center library events publications contact & maps information for prospective students alumni employers current students faculty & staff news center stanford law review goes online go back publication date november 11 2011 source the stanford daily author brendan o byrne the stanford law review is mentioned in this daily report article by brendan o byrne on it's move to an online platform where it will feature short original and timely scholarship and commentary by top flight scholars and practitioners the stanford law review slr launched an online version thursday intended to provide an outlet for law review quality pieces with internet speed turnaround between submission and publication according to a statement on its website the site will feature shorter timelier articles on legal topics in the news currently planned articles include an analysis of california's criminal sentencing commissions constitution making and the arab spring the lehman brothers bankruptcy and the protect ip act among others law student james freedman a graduate of johns hopkins university will serve as senior online editor of the journal he has previously served as senior production editor of the stanford law review and co president of the stanford law and technology association law professor robert weisberg 79 authored the first piece posted on the site titled california's de facto sentencing commissions full story related faculty robert weisberg related stanford law and technology association slata stanford law review rain 54 f 2012 stanford university system requirements help virtual tour
